<TITLE> Bomb attack injures 2 policemen </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)  Two policemen were injuried, one of them critically, when unidentified assailants hurled a bomb at them at Sutrapur in the city on Saturday evening. The injured assistant sub-inspector Moshiur Rahman and constable Saiful Islam had been rushed to Rajarbagh Police Hospital and Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Sutrapur police sub-inspector Abdur Razzak said miscreants suddenly hurled a bomb at the two policemen at around 7:15pm when they were patrolling Dayaganj area under Sutrapur. The policemen were first rushed to Rajarbagh Police Hospital but one of them was later shifted Dhaka Medical College Hospital in critical condition. Moshiur sustained injuries on his head and left thigh and Saiful on his belly. Saiful received first aid. Minister of state for home affairs Tanjim Ahmed visited DMCH to see Moshiur and inquired about his condition. The state minister, better known as Sohel Taj, told reporters there the government would "try to extend security to all and my visit reflects the government's intention." bd
